The paper deals with the problem of mining communities in social networks based on specific attributes, which is a common topic in the field of social network analysis. The use of concerned attributes to expand feature subspaces is a technique commonly used in machine learning and data mining, which suggests the paper may belong to the sub-categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing). The paper also proposes an algorithm to optimize the subspace fitness, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The application of the proposed method on real-world networks suggests the paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
